    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for Model Risk Level 2. The CFD model demonstrates adequate predictive accuracy for relative hemolysis index across the full CPB operating envelope. Mesh independence (GCI < 2.1%), code verification against established benchmarks, and direct validation against experimental hemolysis data collectively support the credibility claim. The 6 non-assessed factors are appropriate for MRL 2 and do not represent gaps in the credibility argument. The model is accepted for use in identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device submission.",
